SECTION 10 — CRITICAL RULES
════════════════════════════════════════════════════

C-1  TOPIC NAMES ARE GROUND TRUTH FROM DOCS.
     If the Unitree documentation shows a different topic name than what is
     currently in the codebase, update the code to match the documentation.
     Never assume simulation names match hardware names.

C-2  LIDAR TILT DECISION IS DATA-DRIVEN.
     Read the URDF lidar_link RPY. Check the docs for driver compensation.
     Implement the static transform based on measured values, not assumptions.
     If the URDF shows rpy="0 -0.26 0" (approx 15° forward tilt), that tilt
     must be reflected in the static transform from lidar_link to unilidar_lidar.
     If the URDF shows rpy="0 0 0", identity transform is correct.

C-3  JOYSTICK OVERRIDE IS HARD AND UNCONDITIONAL.
     Once joystick_safety_node is launched (use_joystick_safety=true),
     the override is always active. No runtime parameter disables it.
     It is a safety measure, not a convenience feature.

C-4  DO NOT FIGHT THE PHYSICAL CONTROLLER.
     While the human operator moves the joystick, the Go2's internal controller
     handles the robot. The ROS2 stack must be completely silent: no Move(),
     no StopMove() sent while /joystick_override is True.
     The go2_hw_bridge watchdog will eventually fire its own StopMove, which
     is harmless since the physical controller ignores it.

C-5  STARTUP SEQUENCE IS ONE-SHOT PER PROCESS.
     The startup_done_ flag prevents re-sending ClassicWalk if the node
     restarts mid-operation. It fires once per process lifetime.

C-6  PRESERVE EXISTING TOPIC NAMES.
     /cmd_vel, /odom, /scan, /map, /robot_status must remain unchanged.
     Only ADD new topics (/joystick_override).

C-7  VERIFY, DO NOT ASSUME, DDS DOMAIN AND RMW.
     Mismatch in DDS domain or RMW implementation is the single most common
     cause of "ros2 topic list is empty on companion PC" on real hardware.
     Document the correct values in hw_notes_verified.md and in the checklist.
